@startuml Basic Story Generation Sequence
' Basic Story Generation Flow
' Shows the core text-to-story generation process

actor User
participant "Frontend" as FE
participant "FastAPI Backend" as API
participant "Director Agent" as Director
participant "Prompt Agent" as Prompt
participant "Writer Agent" as Writer
participant "Reviewer Agent" as Reviewer
participant "Editor Agent" as Editor
participant "Ollama LLM" as LLM

User -> FE: Enter story prompt
User -> FE: Click "Generate Story"
FE -> API: POST /api/generate
API -> Director: Start pipeline
Director -> Prompt: Validate & enhance prompt
Prompt -> Prompt: Classify prompt type
Prompt -> Director: Enhanced prompt + classification

alt Prompt is valid
    Director -> Writer: Generate story structure
    Writer -> LLM: Generate story with llama3.1:8b
    LLM -> Writer: Story JSON response
    Writer -> Director: Structured story data
    
    Director -> Reviewer: Review story quality
    Reviewer -> Reviewer: Check age-appropriateness
    Reviewer -> Reviewer: Validate coherence
    Reviewer -> Director: Approved story
    
    Director -> Editor: Polish and format
    Editor -> Editor: Refine language
    Editor -> Editor: Generate PDF
    Editor -> Director: Final story + PDF
    
    Director -> API: Complete story response
    API -> FE: Story data with metadata
    FE -> User: Display story with navigation
else Prompt is invalid
    Prompt -> Director: Error classification
    Director -> API: Error response
    API -> FE: Error message
    FE -> User: Show error, request new prompt
end

@enduml
